Schinus molle

   [9612.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Anacardiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names pepper tree, qundo berbere (Amargna), peperboom
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 9612

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Webb D 1984 pp 241 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, SAL, LIG, DEP, KTMP,
   USE]
   Sims D (pers. comm.)
   Duke J 1975 pp 26 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 254 [USE]
   INSPIRE species 158 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, SAL, LIG, USE]
   Hensleight T 1988 pp 385 [TEMP, RAIN, PH, DRA, SAL, USE]
   KILLING T
   Moderately frost tender.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Rather slow growing perennial evergreen tree. Withstands droughts of
   4-8 months.
   COMMON NAMES
   Pepper tree, Molle, Brazilian pepper tree, California peppertree.
   FURTHER INF
   Pepper tree can be found at elevations from 1000 to 3500 m. The
   latitudinal range of natural occurrence is 23-25Â°S. The tree can reach
   a height of 10-15 m. It is drought hardy, termite resistant, it
   tolerates salt winds and requires wide spacing. Mentioned as a possible
   agroforestry species. Annual wood production potential is 3-5 m3/ha.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
